This paper discusses a decision tree learning algorithm for multiclass classification, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it analyzes the performance of the algorithm and its objective function, which is relevant to topics such as optimization and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the algorithm may have applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI), which are also possible sub-categories.
